Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic was created using Canva, an easy-to-use online design platform. The infographic highlights key aspects of digital literacy including its definition, importance for students, safe internet practices, and essential digital tools like Google Workspace and GitHub. The design uses simple icons, short text, and a clean layout to make the information visually engaging and easy to understand for students.

The infographic explains how digital literacy helps students in academics, communication, and career growth. It also emphasizes safe browsing habits such as avoiding suspicious links, using strong passwords, and protecting personal information online. Additionally, it includes a section on email etiquette to promote professional communication.

One interesting part of creating this infographic was selecting the right layout and balancing visuals with content. Initially, it was difficult to keep the design simple while including all important information. However, Canva’s templates and design tools made it easier to organize ideas effectively. This task helped improve my understanding of digital awareness and visual communication.
